m10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Yet another beginning...</span><hr size=1> Casidy had been sitting in the corner of the room, playing. She was a bard, and it was her night to entertain the audience. She made good tips in this place, and the later and drunker the audience got the easier they were parted with their money.<br>
<br>
She had noticed the tension as the dark ones had entered the Inn, and how the paladins had covered their swords with their hands in preparation.<br>
<br>
Fights were bad for business, and bad for her tips.<br>
<br>
She saw the dark elf slide up close to the Innkeep and whisper something, no doubt a threat of some sort to his ear, as the color drained from his face. Casidy was not the only one to see this, the tension in the room could be cut with a knife.<br>
<br>
Sighing softly to herself, why does it always have to happen on my night she thought. A plan quickly formed in her mind how to dissipate the building tension, she just hoped that the dark ones would go along with her plan.<br>
<br>
While she had her resolve firmly in hand, she rose quickly and ran up to embrace the one speaking at the counter. Throwing her arms around the strangers neck, she purred out &quot;Cousin, what brings you to these parts, and on my entertaining night?&quot; winking softly to the person in her arms, but feeling a blade slide up to touch her ribs. <br>
<br>
&quot;Have you been so desiring of my music to travel so far and long to hear me play?&quot; Her eyes pleading with the dark one to follow her story.<br>
<br>
Turning to the Innkeep, Casidy threw on her best smile. &quot;Innkeep, a round for my cousins, and the best room in the house. I, of course, will cover the cost.&quot;<br>
<br>
